com.robix.nexway
Class PodScript

java.lang.Object
  com.robix.nexway.PodScript
public class PodScript
extends java.lang.Object

Simple container which represents a Pod script. Useful for reading/writing scripts to/from a file.

writePodScript

                                  java.lang.String fileName)

Writes a PodScript object to the specified file.

If the specified file does not exist, it is created. If the specified file exists, it is overwritten.

The recommended extension for pod scripts is ".rbxScript".

Parameters:
script - the script
fileName - the name of the file to write
Throws:
IOException - if an I/O error occurs
com.robix.internal.RbxIOException

writePodScript

public static void writePodScript(java.lang.String scriptText,
                                  java.lang.String scriptName,
                                  java.lang.String fileName)
                           throws com.robix.internal.RbxIOException
This is a convenience method that writes a PodScript to a file using the specified script text and name.

If the specified file does not exist, it is created. If the specified file exists, it is overwritten.

The behavior of this method is exactly the same as calling: 

 writePodScript( new PodScript( scriptText, scriptName ), fileName );
The recommended extension for pod scripts is ".rbxScript".

Parameters:
scriptText - the script text
scriptName - the script name
fileName - the name of the file to write
Throws:
IOException - if an I/O error occurs
com.robix.internal.RbxIOException
